    "body": "See https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/GMT.jl/issues/827\r\n\r\nIn fact this woks\r\n```\r\nlegend(region=(0,10,0,8), (symbol1=(dx_left=0.25, marker=\"-\", size=0.33, pen=2, fill=:black, dx_right=0.75, text=\"1s delay time\"), symbol2=(dx_left=0.25, marker=:star, size=0.5, pen=:false, fill=:yellow, dx_right=0.75, text=\"Epicentre\")), position=(inside=:BL, anchor=:BL, width=5), box=(; pen=0.5), Vd=1, show=1)\r\n        pslegend  -R0/10/0/8 -JX12c/0 -Baf -BWSen -F+p0.5 -DjBL+w5 -P -K > C:\\TEMP\\GMTjl_tmp.ps\r\n```\r\nbut crashes if I remove the ``width=5``. On an attentive look ``pslegend's`` man page says ``width`` is mandatory but the code should check that because as is\r\n```\r\nif (Ctrl->D.dim[GMT_X] == 0.0) {\t/* Compute legend width */\r\n\t\tlegend_item = gmt_M_memory (GMT, NULL, n_records, struct PSLEGEND_TXT);\t/* Array to hold all labels */\r\n\t\tdo_width = true;\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\nbut later the ``legend_item`` is accessed without checking.\r\n\r\n\r\nFunny, with a  debug build the above working code errors with\r\n```\r\nlegend(region=(0,10,0,8), (symbol1=(dx_left=0.25, marker=\"-\", size=0.33, pen=2, fill=:black, dx_right=0.75, text=\"1s delay time\"), symbol2=(dx_left=0.25, marker=:star, size=0.5, pen=:false, fill=:yellow, dx_right=0.75, text=\"Epicentre\")), position=(inside=:BL, anchor=:BL, width=10), box=(; pen=0.5), Vd=1)\r\n        pslegend  -R0/10/0/8 -JX12c/0 -Baf -BWSen -F+p0.5 -DjBL+w10 -P -K > C:\\TEMP\\GMTjl_tmp.ps\r\npslegend [ERROR]: Option -B parsing failure. Correct syntax:\r\n\r\n...\r\npslegend [ERROR]: Offending option -BWSen\r\n```\r\n",
